<item>
            <title>[LU-3619] llapi_error format does not need a \n</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3619</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Multiple llapi_error() call use a useless format with \n at the end.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="19946">LU-3619</key>
            <summary>llapi_error format does not need a \n</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=11303&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="4" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/priorities/minor.svg">Minor</priority>
                        <status id="1" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/statuses/open.png" description="The issue is open and ready for the assignee to start work on it.">Open</status>
                    <statusCategory id="2" key="new" colorName="default"/>
                                    <resolution id="-1">Unresolved</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="pjones">Peter Jones</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="cealustre">CEA</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Tue, 23 Jul 2013 12:38:23 +0000</created>
                <updated>Wed, 5 Aug 2020 13:32:56 +0000</updated>
                                            <version>Lustre 2.5.0</version>
                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="62976" author="jcl" created="Thu, 25 Jul 2013 14:54:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;when calling  llapi_error(), we provide a string format. As llapi_error() always add a \n to the format, this string we must not have one inside.&lt;br/&gt;
One exemple is:&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_error(LLAPI_MSG_ERROR, rc, &quot;Can&apos;t create pipe\n&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
must be replaced by&lt;br/&gt;
llapi_error(LLAPI_MSG_ERROR, rc, &quot;Can&apos;t create pipe&quot;); &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="62957" author="pjones" created="Thu, 25 Jul 2013 02:24:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;JC&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please elaborate a little?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
